1. whoami – show the current username.

2. id – display your user ID (UID), group ID (GID), and groups.

3. groups – list the groups you belong to.

4. ps aux – show all running processes.

5. top (or htop) – monitor processes and resource usage in real time.

6. kill <PID> – send a signal to a process (by default, terminate it).

7. sudo apt update – refresh the package list (Ubuntu/Debian).

8. sudo apt install <package> – install a package.

9. date – show the current date and time.

10.uptime – show how long the system has been running and the load average.

11. df -h – display disk usage in a human-readable format.

12. free -h – display memory usage in a human-readable format.
